class Solution {
    public boolean canBeEqual(int[] target, int[] arr) {
        Arrays.sort(target);
        Arrays.sort(arr);
        return Arrays.equals(target, arr);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Sorting both arrays and comparing them allows us to check if they contain the same elements, which is a necessary and sufficient condition for being able to transform one into the other through subarray reversals.

